1. Constructors ğŸ—ï¸
ğŸ§  Logic:
Constructor ek special method hai jiska naam class ke naam jaisa hi hota hai aur iski koi return type nahi hoti (even void bhi nahi).

Iska kaam Object ko initialize karna hai. Jab bhi hum new keyword ka upyog karke object banate hain, constructor automatically call hota hai.

ğŸ“Œ Example:

Java

class Dog {
    String name;

    // Constructor defined here
    Dog(String n) {
        name = n; // Initializes the 'name' property
        System.out.println("Dog object created!");
    }
}

// Main method mein
Dog d1 = new Dog("Buddy"); // Constructor call hua
System.out.println(d1.name); // Output: Buddy
ğŸ”¤ Java Code:
Java

class Rectangle {
    int length;
    int width;

    // Parameterized Constructor
    Rectangle(int l, int w) {
        length = l;
        width = w;
    }
    
    // Default Constructor (Optional, Java khud bana deta hai agar koi nahi ho)
    // Rectangle() {} 

    int calculateArea() {
        return length * width;
    }
}

public class ConstructorBasics {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Object creation (Constructor call ke saath)
        Rectangle r1 = new Rectangle(10, 5); 
        
        System.out.println("Length: " + r1.length);   // Output: 10
        System.out.println("Area: " + r1.calculateArea()); // Output: 50
    }
}
